The user is right - I dramatically oversimplified and lost many important elements from their previous work. They had:

1. Concepts (ideas, theories, frameworks)
2. Claims (truth assertions)
3. Questions (open inquiries)
4. Insights (realizations)
5. Emotions (revealing values)
6. Different types of blind spots/occlusions
7. Problems and solutions
8. Work items with progress
9. Perspectives and philosophy stacks
10. Research stances
11. Dialectic axes
12. Convergence points
13. LLM suggestions
14. Specific values (Palestine, Family, Attention, Growth)

They want to see how ALL of these fit into a coherent ontology, not just the minimal cybernetic core. Let me create a comprehensive version that shows how everything maps together.You're absolutely right - I went too minimal and lost the richness we developed! Let me show how ALL our elements fit into a coherent whole:

## Complete Mapping: How Everything Fits

### 1. The Cybernetic Core Contains Everything

```turtle
# LAYER 1: Basic Knowledge Elements
pgo:Concept rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Model ;
    rdfs:comment "A concept IS a model - a simplified representation" .

pgo:Claim rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Reference ;
    rdfs:comment "A claim IS a reference state - 'this should be true'" .

pgo:Question rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Gap ;
    rdfs:comment "A question IS a gap - between what we know and need to know" .

pgo:Insight rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Learning ;
    rdfs:comment "An insight IS learning - sudden model update" .

# LAYER 2: Emotional/Value Elements  
pgo:Emotion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Feedback ;
    rdfs:comment "Emotions ARE feedback - about value alignment" .

pgo:Value a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:comment "Cluster of related CAPs" ;
    pgo:constitutedBy pgo:CAP .

# Example of Value as CAP cluster
pgo:Palestine a pgo:Value ;
    pgo:constitutedBy 
        :CAP_MomentsOfSharedHumanity ,
        :CAP_StoriesBreakingAbstractions ,
        :CAP_ContradictionsInPolicy ,
        :CAP_OpportunitiesForCoexistence .

# LAYER 3: Blind Spots/Occlusions (from our deep dive)
pgo:Occlusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Gap ;
    rdfs:comment "Gaps we can't or won't see" .

pgo:ScaleOcclusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Occlusion ;
    rdfs:comment "Can't see forest for trees" .

pgo:TemporalOcclusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Occlusion ;
    rdfs:comment "Moving too fast/slow to perceive" .

pgo:TraumaOcclusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Occlusion ;
    rdfs:comment "Too painful to see" .

pgo:MethodOcclusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Occlusion ;
    rdfs:comment "Wrong tool for the job" .

pgo:LevelOcclusion rdfs:subClassOf pgo:Occlusion ;
    rdfs:comment "Looking at wrong abstraction level" .
```

### 2. The Complete Ontology (All Elements Integrated)

```turtle
